    <theorem xml:id="thm-kernel-is-ideal">
<idx><h>kernel</h><h>is an ideal</h></idx>
	  <statement>
		<p>
		  Given a ring homomorphism <m>\phi : R\to S</m>,
		  <m>\ker\phi</m> is an ideal.
		</p>
	  </statement>
	  <proof>
		<p>
		  If <m>x,y\in \ker\phi</m>, <m>\phi(x+y) = \phi(x) + \phi(y) = 0_S + 0_S = 0_S</m>.
		  Similarly, if <m>x\in \ker \phi</m> and <m>r\in R</m>, <m>\phi(rx) = \phi(r) \phi(x) = \phi(r) 0_S = 0_S</m>.
		</p>
	  </proof>
	</theorem>

  <p>
    As we see in <xref ref="thm-kernel-is-ideal" />, the kernel of a ring homomorphism is an ideal.
  </p>

